OL,3,C62% of Guernsey's poorest homes do not
OL,4,Chave enough beds, report finds
OL,6,FThirty-eight percent of the island's
OL,7,Fpoorest household do not have enough
OL,8,Fbeds for the number of people living
OL,9,Fthere, with cost attributed as one
OL,10,Fcause but a lack of space also playing
OL,11,Fa part.
OL,13,FSimilarly, more than half of those
OL,14,Fpoorest households do not have carpets
OL,15,For other types of floor coverings in
OL,16,Fevery room.
OL,18,FThere is no universally agreed
OL,19,Fdefinition for what poverty is
OL,20,Falthough the States of Guernsey, and
OL,21,Fthe report, refer to relative poverty.
