OL,3,C62% of Guernsey's poorest homes do not
OL,4,Chave enough beds, report finds
OL,6,FThis is where a household's income is
OL,7,Fless than 60% of what is the median
OL,8,Fhousehold income, after tax, social
OL,9,Fsecurity and housing costs.
OL,11,FFor example, the report says a two-
OL,12,Fadult household in Guernsey is living
OL,13,Fin relative poverty if they are left
OL,14,Fwith less than #22,318 per year after
OL,15,Fthose costs are taken away.
OL,17,FThe document also highlights that 22%
OL,18,Fof pensioners live in relative poverty
OL,19,Fwith 40% of single pensioners falling
OL,20,Fwithin that parameter.
