OL,6,F"You find yourself just trying to
OL,7,Fscrimp through the cupboards and find
OL,8,Fwhat you can.
OL,10,F"Sometimes when we're thinking about
OL,11,Fwhat we're having for tea, we have to
OL,12,Fsay, if it's there, we can have it, if
OL,13,Fit's not, you can't."
OL,15,FAlly added that she believes it is a
OL,16,F"struggle" to cover the cost of other
OL,17,Fbasics in the home including heating,
OL,18,Ffor the vast majority of islanders.
